detail.title: Yellow Spaceship Upgrade
detail.description:
# AssetMantle v1 Yellow Spaceship Upgrade

       This is a proposal to do a software upgrade to the v1.0.0 software tag of the AssetMantle codebase at block height 7135001, which is estimated to occur on Tuesday, August 18 UTC 17:30. Block times have high variance, so please monitor the chain for more precise time estimates.

       # Yellow Spaceship Upgrade adds the following features:

             * Classifications: Allows definig different class of assets, identities and orders
             * Assets: Enabling minting, burning, renumerate and mutation of digital assets.
             * Identities: Establishing a robust decentralized-identity framework to ensure secure and verified user interactions, reinforcing trust and accountability.
             * Maintainers: Empowering designated maintainers to oversee specific processes, facilitating efficient and reliable protocol maintenance & operation.
             * Metas: Introducing metadata management for assets and transactions, enhancing data privacy and accessibility.
             * Orders: Implementing a dynamic order system to enable exchange of assets.
             * Splits: Manages the ownership and transfer of assets

       The release can be found here: https://github.com/AssetMantle/node/releases

       We recommend validators utilize 64GB of RAM. Since there is only addition of new modules, it is likely possible to get away with less, but still not recommended. If you are unable to have 64GB of RAM, at a minimum have a total of 64GB of swap set to prevent out of memory errors.

       # Details of Upgrade Time:

:       The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 7135001, anticipated to be on August 18th, 2023, UTC 12:00. Note that block times have high variance, so keep monitoring the time. See countdown: https://www.mintscan.io/asset-mantle/blocks/7135001       The upgrade is anticipated to take approximately 30 minutes, during which time, there will not be any on-chain activity on the network.       In the event of an issue at upgrade time, we should coordinate via the Discord [https://discord.com/invite/BSdBQ4495d] to come to a quick emergency consensus and mitigate any further issues.

detail.title: Increase min deposit param
detail.description: Huge amount of spam/scam proposals have been submitted in the past day and MNTL price currently allows to spam the chain with fake proposals very cheapy. We have decided to propose the community to increase the min amount of MNTL that should be deposited for a governance proposal from 512 MNTL to 50000 MNTL (~350$ considering a MNTL price of 0.0069$). This should make it less likely for bad actors to create scam or spam proposals in the future, preserving the real meaning of on-chain governance.

detail.title: Allocate Community Pool Funds to incentivise MNTL pool liquidity providers on Osmosis and creation of multi-sig wallet
detail.description:
This proposal is intended to further boost MNTL liquidity on the Osmosis AMM, As part of our ongoing commitment to expanding the accessibility of MNTL to a diversified set of users. Currently, on Osmosis, MNTL is paired with ATOM, OSMO, and USDC tokens.

By voting "YES" on this proposal, 1,500,000 MNTL from the community pool will be allocated to incentivize the MNTL/OSMO pool, 750,000 MNTL to the MNTL/ATOM pool, and 750,000 MNTL to the MNTL/USDC pool on Osmosis.

By voting "NO" on this proposal, the community dissents on allocating the aforementioned allocations to the respective pools on Osmosis.

Details: Users/LPs bonding their $MNTL LP token  on Osmosis will be incentivized through the community pool's 3,000,000 MNTL. Distribution: ~50,000 MNTL per day, or ~$610 (@ $0.012) per day for 60 days.

How it would work:

The proposal time period will be 7 days.

If the proposal is passed, the funds will be moved to a 2/3 multisig wallet.

The funds will then be deposited on Osmosis AMM, which will be used to incentivize the LPs for 90 Epochs.

Signers of the 2/3 Multisig wallet:

AsGuard

Citadel.One

Cros-nest

Who will perform the IBC transfer and deposit to the Osmosis liquidity gauges, after this point the funds are entirely non-custodial. Wallet Address:

mantle1xr0clmqtl2yxeq05y8f6az56ugh7lqyvmw6r7g

detail.title: Increase Max Validators to 70
detail.description:
This proposal marks the completion of 3rd quarter of operations of the mantle-1 mainnet.  Since its genesis, the mantle-1 chain has been running stably with no major consensus failures or attacks and has grown to see 96k+ unique wallets and 6.5m+ on-chain transactions. The chain has been clocking in the top 10 chains in cosmos w.r.t weekly active users, IBC transactions and in developer activity. The MantleChain Foundation Delegation Program has evaluated more than 200 applications so far. It has been actively making delegation decisions based purely on the contributions from the validators across technical, community building, and ecosystem expansion fronts. Even so, many great validators are willing to contribute to the project but are unable to participate, being restricted by the 65 max validators count on the chain.

This proposal intends to increase the active validator set of the mantle chain by 5 (MaxValidators=65 to MaxValidators=70).

This proposal is mechanically generated by the AssetMantle team, following the initial chain stabilization plan, for each of the first 5 quarters of chain operation to:

Retire 1 Foundation node

Increase validator set by 5 

Re-evaluate foundation delegations for the last quarter and accordingly increase/decrease/remove delegations 

Open five new spots in the foundation delegation program 

The AssetMantle team's vision for the chain is to become a fully community-governed and truly decentralized chain for the next two years. Adding these new validator spots will help increase active participation from the community and further diversify the validator set to enhance chain security. 

To apply for the new spots added to the foundation delegation program - https://info.assetmantle.one/AM-PostGenesis-Validators

detail.title: Increase MaxValidators=55 to MaxValidators=65
detail.description: The AssetMantle ecosystem has a quick adaptation and has a very important milestone for its community. Additionally AssetMantle has proven to be a futuristic network maintained and operated by trusted and well known validators. AssetMantle's trusted active set validators should not have to make an effort to stay in the active set, and in addition that , They should be enabled for new trusted node operators to be in the active set. For the short and medium term development and awareness of AssetMantle, increasing the number of active set validators from 55 to 65 will be much more suitable for the entire AssetMantle ecosystem. As AssetMantle has proven its stability and trustworthiness  since its genesis, AssetMantle will be believed to have reached a level of quality and decentralized to be continuining a larger set of validators.

detail.title: Increase active validator set from 50 to 55
detail.description:
The AssetMantle mainnet went live on the 18th of April 2022 and will be completing its first annual quarter 7 days from this proposal. Since its genesis, the mantle-1 chain has been running stably with no major consensus failures or attacks and has grown to see 93k+ active wallets and 3.5m+ on-chain transactions. The MantleChain Foundation Delegation Program has evaluated more than 190 applications so far. It has been actively making delegation decisions based purely on the contributions from the validators across technical, community building, and ecosystem expansion fronts. Even so, many great validators are willing to contribute to the project but are unable to participate, being restricted by the 50 max validators count on the chain.

This proposal intends to increase the active validator set of the mantle chain by 5 (MaxValidators=50 to MaxValidators=55).

This is a proposal mechanically generated by the AssetMantle team, following the initial chain stabilization plan, for each of the first 5 quarters of chain operation to:

1. Retire 1 Foundation node

2. Increase validator set by 5

3. Re-evaluate foundation delegations for the last quarter and accordingly increase/decrease/remove delegations

4. Open five new spots in the foundation delegation program

The AssetMantle team's vision for the chain is to become a fully community-governed and truly decentralized chain for the next two years. Adding these new validator spots will help increase active participation from the community and further diversify the validator set to enhance chain security.

To apply for the new spots added to the foundation delegation program - https://info.assetmantle.one/AM-PostGenesis-Validators
